Explanation

- There is no class-level @RequestMapping that would add a prefix, so the full path is exactly "/consumer/budget".
- No annotation or mapping in the code enables any other HTTP methods for that path. Per your instruction to rely on the code (not runtime/container behavior), HEAD is not considered acceptable because there is no explicit mapping for HEAD or corresponding GET on the same path in the source.
- The method is also protected with @Secured("ROLE_USER"), but that affects authorization, not which HTTP methods are mapped.
